  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      68.25,
      290.6,
      537.3,
      309.98
    ],
    "text": "appellant was arrested with a parcel of heroin inside his trouser pocket.",
    "fonts": [
      "Helvetica"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.100000381469727,
      14.160271644592285,
      14.560287475585938
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      68.75,
      319.87,
      429.9,
      339.25
    ],
    "text": "In King V. Musthapha 44 N.L.R 505 the Court held thus:-",
    "fonts": [
      "Helvetica"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      13.541905403137207,
      13.790605545043945,
      13.829352378845215,
      14.035201072692871,
      14.100000381469727,
      14.17748737335205
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      68.61,
      348.91,
      539.78,
      389.41
    ],
    "text": "liThe Court of Criminal Appeal will not interfere with the verdict of a Jury unless it has a real doubt as to the guilt of the accused or is of the opinion",
    "fonts": [
      "Helvetica"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      13.281599044799805,
      13.532635688781738,
      13.922229766845703,
      14.100000381469727,
      14.108448028564453,
      14.160271644592285,
      14.239212989807129,
      14.359707832336426,
      14.424858093261719,
      14.560287475585938,
      14.57993221282959
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      68.33,
      391.39,
      540.59,
      410.77
    ],
    "text": "that on the whole it is safer that the conviction should not be allowed to",
    "fonts": [
      "Helvetica"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      13.337904930114746,
      14.100000381469727,
      14.14956283569336,
      14.2811861038208,
      14.446785926818848,
      14.589454650878906
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      68.51,
      413.0,
      118.51,
      432.38
    ],
    "text": "stand.\"",
    "fonts": [
      "Helvetica"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.100000381469727
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      68.41,
      442.28,
      541.43,
      482.77
    ],
    "text": "A Court of Appeal will not lightly disturb the findings of a trial Judge with regard to the acceptance or rejection of testimony of a witness unless it",
    "fonts": [
      "Helvetica"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.100000381469727,
      14.109196662902832,
      14.174653053283691,
      14.424858093261719,
      14.446785926818848,
      14.560287475585938,
      14.589454650878906
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      69.11,
      483.78,
      539.24,
      503.92
    ],
    "text": "is manifestly wrong. In Privy Council V. Fradd V. Brown & Company Ltd.",
    "fonts": [
      "Helvetica",
      "Times-Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      13.337904930114746,
      13.541905403137207,
      13.679428100585938,
      13.829352378845215,
      14.100000381469727,
      15.100000381469727
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      69.0,
      505.87,
      262.88,
      525.25
    ],
    "text": "20 N.L.R 282 it was held that:-",
    "fonts": [
      "Helvetica"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      13.84234619140625,
      14.005382537841797,
      14.100000381469727,
      14.101700782775879,
      14.589454650878906
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      69.09,
      534.91,
      541.67,
      554.29
    ],
    "text": "lilt is rare that decision of a Judge so express, so explicit upon a point of",
    "fonts": [
      "Helvetica"
